cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
title: "Semantic Mode Theory"
abstract: >-
  A preliminary research program studying how meaning is formed, distorted,
  collapses, and recovers in brains and in large language models, treated as a
  dynamic mode structure. It pairs an explanatory pillar (Semantic Mode Theory)
  with an empirical pillar (a stress-testing framework) connected by a
  prediction-observation loop. Working hypotheses, not peer-reviewed results.
